Introduction

Victoria Song (or simply Victoria) is a Chinese singer, actress, and model under Song Qian Studio. She studied ethnic Chinese dance at Bejing Dance Academy after her graduation, and in 2007, she was scouted by SM during a dance competition. Victoria debuted as an idol in 2009 with SM's 5-member South Korean girl group f(x) as their Leader, Main Dancer, Lead Rapper, Sub Vocalist, and Visual.

Through this group, she steadily rose to fame in Korea. She starred in the 2012 Chinese and Tawainese co-production drama 'When Love Walked In' which scored the number 1 spot in viewership ratings and led her to win the Best New Actress awards at the China TV Drama Awards.

In 2018, she debuted as a solo artist with the single 'Roof of Fire' and continued her solo singing career with the 2020 self-titled album 'Victoria' which sold 250 000 copies within 22 hours of its release, leading her to become the fastest Chinese female artist to reach diamond certification on QQ Music in 2020. The album reached #1 place on QQ Music after selling over 300,000 copies in the first weeks.

In April 2021, Victoria left SM Entertainment after her contract expired.
